A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Titles 31, 33, and 43 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to health,
2 insurance, and professions and businesses, respectively, so as to provide for medically
3 necessary tests for metal allergies and metal sensitivities to be administered prior to any
4 cardiovascular, dental, or orthopedic surgery involving the insertion of a metal implant; to
5 provide for definitions; to provide for health benefit policies to cover such tests; to provide
6 for cost-sharing requirements; to provide for rules and regulations; to provide for continuing
7 education requirements for dental surgeons and surgeons; to provide for requirements for
8 certain healthcare providers; to provide for a private cause of action; to provide for related
9 matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
11 SECTION 1.
12 Title 31 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to health, is amended in Chapter
13 1, relating to general provisions, by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
14 "31-1-26.
15 (a) The department, in consultation with the Georgia Board of Dentistry and the Georgia
16 Composite Medical Board, shall identify and compile information on metal allergies and
