26 all surgeons licensed to practice medicine in this state."
27 SECTION 2.
28 Title 33 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to insurance, is amended in
29 Chapter 24, relating to insurance generally, by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
30 "33-24-59.34.
31 (a) As used in this Code section, the term:
32 (1) 'Cost-sharing requirement' means a deductible, coinsurance, or copayment and any
33 maximum limitation on the application of such deductible, coinsurance, copayment, or
34 similar out-of-pocket expense.
35 (2) 'Health benefit policy' means any individual or group plan, policy, or contract for
36 healthcare services issued, delivered, issued for delivery, or renewed in this state which
37 provides major medical benefits, including those contracts executed by the State of
38 Georgia on behalf of indigents and on behalf of state employees under Article 1 of
39 Chapter 18 of Title 45, by a healthcare corporation, health maintenance organization,
40 preferred provider organization, accident and sickness insurer, fraternal benefit society,
41 hospital service corporation, medical service corporation, or any similar entity and any
