42 self-insured healthcare plan not subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the Employee
43 Retirement Income Security Act of 1974, 29 U.S.C. Section 1001, et seq.
44 (3) 'Medically necessary' shall have the same meaning as set forth in Code Section
45 33-46-4 and shall be in accordance with guidelines established pursuant to Code Section
46 31-1-26; provided, however, that, if a patient informs a healthcare provider that he or she
47 has a metal allergy or metal sensitivity, a lymphocyte transformation test or other more
48 advanced test shall be considered medically necessary.
49 (4) 'Metal implant' means any medical device made of metal that is used to support or
50 replace any human body part, including but not limited to any bone, joint, or tooth. Such
51 term shall not include any medical injection, surgical tool, or dental filling.
52 (b) All health benefit policies issued, delivered, issued for delivery, or renewed on or after
53 July 1, 2025, shall include coverage for medically necessary tests for metal allergies and
54 metal sensitivities prior to any cardiovascular, dental, or orthopedic surgery involving the
55 insertion of a metal implant into the human body.
56 (c) The coverage provided for in subsection (b) of this Code section shall be subject to any
57 cost-sharing requirement of the covered person's health benefit policy and shall not
58 diminish or limit any other benefits provided under such policy.
59 (d) If application of the provisions of this Code section would result in health savings
60 account ineligibility under 26 U.S.C. Section 223 as it existed on January 1, 2025, then
61 such provisions shall apply only to health savings accounts with qualified high deductible
62 health plans with respect to the deductibles of such plans after an individual has satisfied
63 the minimum deductibles; provided, however, that the provisions of this Code section shall
64 apply to items or services that are preventive care.
65 (e) The Commissioner shall promulgate rules and regulations necessary to implement the
66 provisions of this Code section."
