67 SECTION 3.
68 Title 43 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to professions and businesses,
69 is amended in Chapter 11, relating to dentists, dental hygienists, and dental assistants, by
70 adding a new subsection to Code Section 43-11-46.1, relating to continuing education
71 requirements and waiver, to read as follows:
72 "(f) On and after January 1, 2025, continuing education requirements for dental surgeons
73 shall include one hour of education and training on metal allergies and metal sensitivities
74 and any medically necessary and recommended tests to be administered prior to any dental
75 surgery involving the insertion of a metal implant into a human body."
76 SECTION 4.
77 Said title is further amended in Chapter 34, relating to physicians, acupuncture, physician
78 assistants, cancer and glaucoma treatment, respiratory care, clinical perfusionists, and
79 orthotics and prosthetics practice, by adding a new paragraph to subsection (a) of Code
80 Section 43-34-11, relating to continuing education requirement and required training for
81 physicians, to read as follows:
82 "(7) On and after January 1, 2025, all surgeons shall be required to receive one hour of
83 education and training on metal allergies and metal sensitivities and any medically
84 necessary and recommended tests to be administered prior to any surgery involving the
85 insertion of a metal implant into a human body."
86 SECTION 5.
87 Said title is further amended in said chapter by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
88 "43-34-16.
89 (a) As used in this Code section, the term:
90 (1) 'Healthcare provider' means a physician or other person licensed or otherwise
91 authorized to perform surgical services in this state.
