92 (2) 'Medically necessary' shall have the same meaning as set forth in Code Section
93 33-46-4 and shall be in accordance with clinical practice guidelines established pursuant
94 to Code Section 31-1-26; provided, however, that, if a patient informs a healthcare
95 provider that he or she has a metal allergy or metal sensitivity, a lymphocyte
96 transformation test or other more advanced test shall be considered medically necessary.
97 (3) 'Metal implant' means any medical device made of metal that is used to support or
98 replace any human body part, including but not limited to any bone, joint, or tooth. Such
99 term shall not include any medical injection, surgical tool, or dental filling.
100 (b) Prior to performing any cardiovascular, dental, or orthopedic surgery involving the
101 insertion of a metal implant into a human body, a healthcare provider shall:
102 (1) Ask a patient if he or she has any metal allergy or metal sensitivity; and
103 (2) Perform any medically necessary tests for metal allergies and metal sensitivities.
104 (c) A patient aggrieved by a healthcare provider's failure to satisfy the requirements
105 provided for in subsection (b) of this Code section may bring a private cause of action
106 against such provider for damages and any other relief a court of competent jurisdiction
107 deems appropriate."
108 SECTION 6.
109 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
